- **Saddam Hussein Abd al-Majid al-Tikriti**  ([/hʊˈseɪn/](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA/English) ;[[3]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saddam_Hussein#cite_note-3)  [Arabic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arabic_alphabet) : صدام حسين عبد المجيد التكريتي  __  __  Ṣaddām Ḥusayn ʿAbd al-Majīd al-Tikrītī __  __  ;[[a]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saddam_Hussein#cite_note-7)  28 April 1935[[b]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saddam_Hussein#cite_note-9)  – 30 December 2006) was an [Iraqi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq)  politician, the fifth [President of Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Iraq)  from 16 July 1979 until 9 April 2003.[[8]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saddam_Hussein#cite_note-10)  A leading member of the revolutionary [Arab Socialist Ba'ath Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ba%27ath_Party) , and later, the [Baghdad-based Ba'ath Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ba%27ath_Party_(Iraqi-dominated_faction) ) and its regional organization, the [Iraqi Ba'ath Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arab_Socialist_Ba%27ath_Party_%E2%80%93_Iraq_Region) —which espoused [Ba'athism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ba%27athism) , a mix of [Arab nationalism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arab_nationalism)  and [Arab socialism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arab_socialism) —Saddam played a key role in the 1968 coup (later referred to as the [17 July Revolution](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/17_July_Revolution) ) that brought the party to power in Iraq.
