- **Muammar Muhammad Abu Minyar al-Gaddafi** [[b]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muammar_Gaddafi#cite_note-14) (c. 1942 – 20 October 2011), commonly known as **Colonel Gaddafi**, was a Libyan revolutionary, politician and political theorist. He governed Libya as Revolutionary Chairman of the [Libyan Arab Republic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_Arab_Republic) from 1969 to 1977 and then as the "[Brotherly Leader](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brotherly_Leader_and_Guide_of_the_Revolution)" of the [Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_Arab_Jamahiriya) from 1977 to 2011. He was initially ideologically committed to [Arab nationalism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arab_nationalism) and [Arab socialism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arab_socialism) but later ruled according to his own [Third International Theory](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Third_International_Theory).
