- **Banda Singh Bahadu**r
    - Birth name = Lachman Dev
    - Born = 27 Oct 1670
    - Died = 9 June 1716
    - was a Sikh warrior and a commander of [Khalsa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khalsa)  army. At age 15, he left home to become an [ascetic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asceticism) , and was given the name **Madho Das Bairagi**
    - He established a monastery at [Nānded](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nanded) , on the bank of the river [Godāvarī](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Godavari) . In 1707, Guru Gobind Singh accepted an invitation to meet [Bahadur Shah I](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bahadur_Shah_I)  in southern India. He visited Banda Singh Bahadur in 1708.
    - Banda became disciple of [Guru Gobind Singh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guru_Gobind_Singh)  and was given a new name, Banda Singh Bahadur, after the Baptism Ceremony.
    - He was given five arrows by the Guru as a blessing for the battles ahead. He came to [Khanda](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khanda,_India)  in [Sonipat](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonipat)  and assembled a fighting force and led the struggle against the [Mughal Empire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mughal_Empire) .
    - His first major action was the sacking of the Mughal provincial capital, [Samana](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samana,_Punjab) , in November 1709.[[1]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banda_Singh_Bahadur#cite_note-eos-1)  After establishing his authority and [Khalsa rule](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misl)  in [Punjab](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjab_(region) ),[[4]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banda_Singh_Bahadur#cite_note-4)
    - Banda Singh Bahadur abolished the [zamindari](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zamindari)   system, and granted property rights to the tillers of the land. Banda  Singh was captured by the Mughals and tortured to death in 1715–1716.
